items.title: Awesome Python Data Science
items.content_text: ### Machine Learning / General Purpose Machine Learning * [scikit-learn](http://scikit-learn.org/stable/) - Machine learning in Python. * [cuML (‚≠ê4.8k)](https://github.com/rapidsai/cuml) - RAPIDS Machine Learning Library. * [modAL (‚≠ê2.3k)](https://github.com/cosmic-cortex/modAL) - Modular active learning framework for Python3. * [Sparkit-learn (‚≠ê1.2k)](https://github.com/lensacom/sparkit-learn) - PySpark + scikit-learn = Sparkit-learn. * [MLxtend (‚≠ê5k)](https://github.com/rasbt/mlxtend) - Extension and helper modules for Python's data analysis and machine learning libraries. * [Reproducible Experiment Platform (REP) (‚≠ê696)](https://github.com/yandex/rep) - Machine Learning toolbox for Humans. * [scikit-multilearn (‚≠ê939)](https://github.com/scikit-multilearn/scikit-multilearn) - Multi-label classification for python. * [seqlearn (‚≠ê697)](https://github.com/larsmans/seqlearn) - Sequence classification toolkit for Python. * [pystruct (‚≠ê668)](https://github.com/pystruct/pystruct) - Simple structured learning framework for Python. * [RuleFit (‚≠ê422)](https://github.com/christophM/rulefit) - Implementation of the rulefit. * [metric-learn (‚≠ê1.4k)](https://github.com/all-umass/metric-learn) - Metric learning algorithms in Python. ### Machine Learning / Ensemble Methods * [ML-Ensemble](http://ml-ensemble.com/) - High performance ensemble learning. * [stacked\_generalization (‚≠ê117)](https://github.com/fukatani/stacked_generalization) - Library for machine learning stacking generalization. * [vecstack (‚≠ê692)](https://github.com/vecxoz/vecstack) - Python package for stacking (machine learning technique). ### Machine Learning / Imbalanced Datasets * [imbalanced-algorithms (‚≠ê239)](https://github.com/dialnd/imbalanced-algorithms) - Python-based implementations of algorithms for learning on imbalanced data. ### Machine Learning / Random Forests * [rpforest (‚≠ê224)](https://github.com/lyst/rpforest) - A forest of random projection trees. * [sklearn-random-bits-forest (‚≠ê9)](https://github.com/tmadl/sklearn-random-bits-forest) - Wrapper of the Random Bits Forest program written by (Wang et al., 2016). * [rgf\_python (‚≠ê381)](https://github.com/fukatani/rgf_python) - Python Wrapper of Regularized Greedy Forest. ### Machine Learning / Kernel Methods * [pyFM (‚≠ê926)](https://github.com/coreylynch/pyFM) - Factorization machines in python. * [fastFM (‚≠ê1.1k)](https://github.com/ibayer/fastFM) - A library for Factorization Machines. * [tffm (‚≠ê781)](https://github.com/geffy/tffm) - TensorFlow implementation of an arbitrary order Factorization Machine. * [scikit-rvm (‚≠ê238)](https://github.com/JamesRitchie/scikit-rvm) - Relevance Vector Machine implementation using the scikit-learn API. * [ThunderSVM (‚≠ê1.6k)](https://github.com/Xtra-Computing/thundersvm) - A fast SVM Library on GPUs and CPUs. ### Deep Learning / PyTorch * [PyTorch (‚≠ê91k)](https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch) - Tensors and Dynamic neural networks in Python with strong GPU acceleration. * [ignite (‚≠ê4.7k)](https://github.com/pytorch/ignite) - High-level library to help with training neural networks in PyTorch. ### Deep Learning / TensorFlow * [TensorFlow (‚≠ê191k)](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow) - Computation using data flow graphs for scalable machine learning by Google. * [TensorLayer (‚≠ê7.4k)](https://github.com/zsdonghao/tensorlayer) - Deep Learning and Reinforcement Learning Library for Researcher and Engineer. * [TFLearn (‚≠ê9.6k)](https://github.com/tflearn/tflearn) - Deep learning library featuring a higher-level API for TensorFlow. * [Sonnet (‚≠ê9.9k)](https://github.com/deepmind/sonnet) - TensorFlow-based neural network library. * [Polyaxon (‚≠ê3.7k)](https://github.com/polyaxon/polyaxon) - A platform that helps you build, manage and monitor deep learning models. * [tensorflow-upstream (‚≠ê694)](https://github.com/ROCmSoftwarePlatform/tensorflow-upstream) - TensorFlow ROCm port. * [TensorFlow Fold (‚≠ê1.8k)](https://github.com/tensorflow/fold) - Deep learning with dynamic computation graphs in TensorFlow. * [TensorLight (‚≠ê11)](https://github.com/bsautermeister/tensorlight) - A high-level framework for TensorFlow. * [Mesh TensorFlow (‚≠ê1.6k)](https://github.com/tensorflow/mesh) - Model Parallelism Made Easier. ### Model Explanation / Others * [Contrastive Explanation (‚≠ê44)](https://github.com/MarcelRobeer/ContrastiveExplanation) - Contrastive Explanation (Foil Trees). * [yellowbrick (‚≠ê4.4k)](https://github.com/DistrictDataLabs/yellowbrick) - Visual analysis and diagnostic tools to facilitate machine learning model selection. * [scikit-plot (‚≠ê2.4k)](https://github.com/reiinakano/scikit-plot) - An intuitive library to add plotting functionality to scikit-learn objects. * [shap (‚≠ê24k)](https://github.com/slundberg/shap) - A unified approach to explain the output of any machine learning model. * [Lime (‚≠ê12k)](https://github.com/marcotcr/lime) - Explaining the predictions of any machine learning classifier. * [FairML (‚≠ê364)](https://github.com/adebayoj/fairml) - FairML is a python toolbox auditing the machine learning models for bias. * [model-analysis (‚≠ê1.3k)](https://github.com/tensorflow/model-analysis) - Model analysis tools for TensorFlow. * [themis-ml (‚≠ê126)](https://github.com/cosmicBboy/themis-ml) - A library that implements fairness-aware machine learning algorithms. * [treeinterpreter (‚≠ê759)](https://github.com/andosa/treeinterpreter) - Interpreting scikit-learn's decision tree and random forest predictions. ### Genetic Programming / Others * [gplearn (‚≠ê1.7k)](https://github.com/trevorstephens/gplearn) - Genetic Programming in Python. * [karoo\_gp (‚≠ê164)](https://github.com/kstaats/karoo_gp) - A Genetic Programming platform for Python with GPU support. * [sklearn-genetic (‚≠ê322)](https://github.com/manuel-calzolari/sklearn-genetic) - Genetic feature selection module for scikit-learn. ### Optimization / Others * [BoTorch (‚≠ê3.3k)](https://github.com/pytorch/botorch) - Bayesian optimization in PyTorch. * [hyperopt-sklearn (‚≠ê1.6k)](https://github.com/hyperopt/hyperopt-sklearn) - Hyper-parameter optimization for sklearn. * [sklearn-deap (‚≠ê774)](https://github.com/rsteca/sklearn-deap) - Use evolutionary algorithms instead of gridsearch in scikit-learn. * [sigopt\_sklearn (‚≠ê75)](https://github.com/sigopt/sigopt_sklearn) - SigOpt wrappers for scikit-learn methods. * [GPflowOpt (‚≠ê272)](https://github.com/GPflow/GPflowOpt) - Bayesian Optimization using GPflow. ### Statistics / NLP * [pandas\_summary (‚≠ê519)](https://github.com/mouradmourafiq/pandas-summary) - Extension to pandas dataframes describe function. * [Pandas Profiling (‚≠ê13k)](https://github.com/pandas-profiling/pandas-profiling) - Create HTML profiling reports from pandas DataFrame objects. * [Alphalens (‚≠ê3.8k)](https://github.com/quantopian/alphalens) - Performance analysis of predictive (alpha) stock factors. ### Computations / Synthetic Data * [Dask (‚≠ê13k)](https://github.com/dask/dask) - Parallel computing with task scheduling. ### Spatial Analysis / Synthetic Data * [GeoPandas (‚≠ê4.8k)](https://github.com/geopandas/geopandas) - Python tools for geographic data.
items.content_html:
Machine Learning / General Purpose Machine Learning

  • scikit-learn - Machine learning in Python.
  • cuML (‚≠ê4.8k) - RAPIDS Machine Learning Library.
  • modAL (‚≠ê2.3k) - Modular active learning framework for Python3.
  • Sparkit-learn (‚≠ê1.2k) - PySpark + scikit-learn = Sparkit-learn.
  • MLxtend (‚≠ê5k) - Extension and helper modules for Python's data analysis and machine learning libraries.
  • Reproducible Experiment Platform (REP) (‚≠ê696) - Machine Learning toolbox for Humans.
  • scikit-multilearn (‚≠ê939) - Multi-label classification for python.
  • seqlearn (‚≠ê697) - Sequence classification toolkit for Python.
  • pystruct (‚≠ê668) - Simple structured learning framework for Python.
  • RuleFit (‚≠ê422) - Implementation of the rulefit.
  • metric-learn (‚≠ê1.4k) - Metric learning algorithms in Python.

Machine Learning / Ensemble Methods

  • ML-Ensemble - High performance ensemble learning.
  • stacked_generalization (‚≠ê117) - Library for machine learning stacking generalization.
  • vecstack (‚≠ê692) - Python package for stacking (machine learning technique).

Machine Learning / Imbalanced Datasets

  • imbalanced-algorithms (‚≠ê239) - Python-based implementations of algorithms for learning on imbalanced data.

Machine Learning / Random Forests

  • rpforest (‚≠ê224) - A forest of random projection trees.
  • sklearn-random-bits-forest (‚≠ê9) - Wrapper of the Random Bits Forest program written by (Wang et al., 2016).
  • rgf_python (‚≠ê381) - Python Wrapper of Regularized Greedy Forest.

Machine Learning / Kernel Methods

  • pyFM (‚≠ê926) - Factorization machines in python.
  • fastFM (‚≠ê1.1k) - A library for Factorization Machines.
  • tffm (‚≠ê781) - TensorFlow implementation of an arbitrary order Factorization Machine.
  • scikit-rvm (‚≠ê238) - Relevance Vector Machine implementation using the scikit-learn API.
  • ThunderSVM (‚≠ê1.6k) - A fast SVM Library on GPUs and CPUs.

Deep Learning / PyTorch

  • PyTorch (‚≠ê91k) - Tensors and Dynamic neural networks in Python with strong GPU acceleration.
  • ignite (‚≠ê4.7k) - High-level library to help with training neural networks in PyTorch.

Deep Learning / TensorFlow

  • TensorFlow (‚≠ê191k) - Computation using data flow graphs for scalable machine learning by Google.
  • TensorLayer (‚≠ê7.4k) - Deep Learning and Reinforcement Learning Library for Researcher and Engineer.
  • TFLearn (‚≠ê9.6k) - Deep learning library featuring a higher-level API for TensorFlow.
  • Sonnet (‚≠ê9.9k) - TensorFlow-based neural network library.
  • Polyaxon (‚≠ê3.7k) - A platform that helps you build, manage and monitor deep learning models.
  • tensorflow-upstream (‚≠ê694) - TensorFlow ROCm port.
  • TensorFlow Fold (‚≠ê1.8k) - Deep learning with dynamic computation graphs in TensorFlow.
  • TensorLight (‚≠ê11) - A high-level framework for TensorFlow.
  • Mesh TensorFlow (‚≠ê1.6k) - Model Parallelism Made Easier.

Model Explanation / Others

  • Contrastive Explanation (‚≠ê44) - Contrastive Explanation (Foil Trees).
  • yellowbrick (‚≠ê4.4k) - Visual analysis and diagnostic tools to facilitate machine learning model selection.
  • scikit-plot (‚≠ê2.4k) - An intuitive library to add plotting functionality to scikit-learn objects.
  • shap (‚≠ê24k) - A unified approach to explain the output of any machine learning model.
  • Lime (‚≠ê12k) - Explaining the predictions of any machine learning classifier.
  • FairML (‚≠ê364) - FairML is a python toolbox auditing the machine learning models for bias.
  • model-analysis (‚≠ê1.3k) - Model analysis tools for TensorFlow.
  • themis-ml (‚≠ê126) - A library that implements fairness-aware machine learning algorithms.
  • treeinterpreter (‚≠ê759) - Interpreting scikit-learn's decision tree and random forest predictions.

Genetic Programming / Others

  • gplearn (‚≠ê1.7k) - Genetic Programming in Python.
  • karoo_gp (‚≠ê164) - A Genetic Programming platform for Python with GPU support.
  • sklearn-genetic (‚≠ê322) - Genetic feature selection module for scikit-learn.

Optimization / Others

  • BoTorch (‚≠ê3.3k) - Bayesian optimization in PyTorch.
  • hyperopt-sklearn (‚≠ê1.6k) - Hyper-parameter optimization for sklearn.
  • sklearn-deap (‚≠ê774) - Use evolutionary algorithms instead of gridsearch in scikit-learn.
  • sigopt_sklearn (‚≠ê75) - SigOpt wrappers for scikit-learn methods.
  • GPflowOpt (‚≠ê272) - Bayesian Optimization using GPflow.

Statistics / NLP

  • Pandas Profiling (‚≠ê13k) - Create HTML profiling reports from pandas DataFrame objects.
  • Alphalens (‚≠ê3.8k) - Performance analysis of predictive (alpha) stock factors.

Spatial Analysis / Synthetic Data
